Again, not a lot of great polling on some of these House races. This is a D+2 district, but of the major forecasters, only Inside Elections is tilting Democrat. Even 538, which is usually much more bullish one way or the other, only has Sorensen (D) leading King (R) 65-35. I expect this to tighten up. 55-45, Sorensen.

I think I had forecasted this wrong originally. Bustos won by 5 points last cycle in a +5 D environment, in a district that leaned +5 R, and that voted for Trump twice. So it looks like she tends to outperform by 5 points. Now her district has shifted +9 D while the national environment has shifted +9 R. So her baseline is still to win by about 5, and she clearly has staying power so far.
This area has shifted RED. Clear Republican win.
While the environment is likely to be friendly to the GOP, the seat is still blue overall and bluer downballot.
